  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRight now we have `subscribeToAllSubnets` flag but it's quite random to pick peers with required subnets (since we only prioritize committee subnets\". In the worse scenario, a node with that flag has very few topic peers\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1066\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-12-19 at 11 21 16\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/208346941-5d2394d9-7983-4861-adab-a84d1cde1fc2.png\">\r\n\r\non another view\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1258\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-12-19 at 11 21 33\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/208346965-c0d5b0f5-04b1-4359-9cc1-55d94a0d99e1.png\">\r\n\r\nit's because most of the peers have 0 long lived subnets\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1290\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-12-19 at 11 22 26\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/208347060-5ab53eb6-4968-4fcc-bd8c-46284b7428cf.png\">\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nWhen we have `subscribeToAllSubnets` flag, we should:\r\n- subscribe to all subnets (already done)\r\n- set to enr `attnets` (already done)\r\n- actively search for peers with all subnets as if we have >= 64 validators connect to our node",
